<div class="news">
<a name="news"></a>
<p class="news-tag">NEWS | DECEMBER 2013</p>
<p class="name">Lab joins the Dana-Farber/Harvard Cancer Center (DF/HCC)</p>
<p class="text">Dr. Arnaout has joined the faculty of the
  Dana-Farber/Harvard Cancer Center. The lab looks forward to closer
  ties with the extraordinary community of the DF/HCC regarding B- and
  T-cell immune repertoires in cancer and in cancer immunotherapy.</p>

<p class="link">
<a class="link" href="http://www.dfhcc.harvard.edu">Visit the DF/HCC website</a>
<br />
</div>

<div class="news">
<a name="news"></a>
<p class="news-tag">NEWS | NOVEMBER 2013</p>
<p class="name">Team charts the dollars and sense behind blood tests</p>
<p class="text">Doctors order too many blood tests, conventional
  wisdom goes, and repeat blood tests are helping bankrupt
  medicine. But is it true? A surprising new 15-year study by
  Dr. Arnaout and colleagues finds widespread underuse, as well as
  overuse, of this single highest-volume medical activity, with repeat
  tests just the tip of the iceberg. The team discusses the
  implications for patients, doctors, and the $3-trillion US
  healthcare economy. Out now in <i>PLoS One</i>.</p>

<p class="link">
<a class="link" href="http://www.plosone.org/article/fetchObject.action?uri=info%3Adoi%2F10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0078962&representation=PDF">Read the full study (PDF)</a>
<br />
<a class="link" href="http://dx.plos.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0078962">Read the full study (HTML)</a>
<br />
<a class="link" href="http://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/health-wellness/2013/11/18/well-asthma-may-delay-pregnancy/Wuv4puPM3fH8Sh6Ukc2nJO/story.html">See <i>Boston Globe</i> coverage</a>
<br />
<a class="link" href="http://www.darkdaily.com/study-at-bostons-beth-israel-deaconess-medical-center-determines-that-30-of-all-clinical-laboratory-tests-are-overused-or-medically-unnecessary-224#axzz2uLPF5P2w">See coverage in <i>Dark Daily</i></a>
<br />
<a class="link" href="http://hms.harvard.edu/news/unnecessary-testing-11-18-13?utm_source=SilverpopMailing&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=11.20.daily%20(1)">See Harvard Medical School coverage</a>
<br />
<a class="link" href="http://www.bostonmagazine.com/health/blog/2013/12/23/hospitals-performing-unnecessary-tests/">See coverage in <i>Boston</i> Magazine</a>
